The BBC’s Jonathan Dimbleby held a panel of leading politicians and thinkers at the University of Nairobi on November 7. Present were Senate majority leader Kipchumba Murkomen, Homa Bay woman representative Gladys Wanga, Siasa Place executive director Nerima Wako and East Africa Centre for Law and Justice executive director Joy Mdivo.  The debate was lead entirely by questions from the audience.  